                            <div class="timeline-body"><p class="text-muted">Alex Adarsh's life on social media was a facade of perfect friendships, creating a deep anxiety about forming real connections. One day, Alex noticed that he was focusing more on digital life than real life so he decided to reduce time on social media, replacing online interactions with church members. Gradually, real conversations and genuine bonds replaced virtual likes, easing Alex's anxiety and revealing the joy of authentic human connections.</p></div>
