                            </div>
                            <div class="timeline-body"><p class="text-muted">Ashley was a graduate student whose research was often interrupted by the lure of social media. To avoid online distractions, Ashley decided to go device-free during study hours. She used pen and paper to outline research ideas, a whiteboard for mapping concepts, and printed materials for references. The physical act of writing helped her stay focused and engaged with the work. This approach not only enhanced Ashley's concentration but also led to the successful completion of a thesis with commendable results.</p></div>
