                                <h4 class="subheading">Confronting Depression</h4>
                            </div>
                            <div class="timeline-body"><p class="text-muted">Seth increasingly found himself depressed due to constantly comparing his life with the idealized lives he saw on social media. He felt inadequate seeing friends' travel photos and colleagues' achievements, creating a cycle of negativity. Realizing this, Seth decided to take action and deleted all social media apps from his phone. He rediscovered old hobbies, like painting, and scheduled regular video chats with friends to maintain social connections. Over time, Seth noticed a marked improvement in his mood and learned to appreciate his own life, free from the constant comparisons.</p></div>
